UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Barbara Henry COPPAGE, Defendant-Appellant. No. 12-10223

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 16, 2012. Barbara Henry Coppage, Bryan, TX, pro se. James Wesley Hendrix, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Dallas, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Before HIGGINBOTHAM, SMITH, and HAYNES, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Barbara Henry Coppage has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967), and United States v. Flores, 632 F.3d 229 (5th Cir.2011). Cop-page has not filed a response. We have reviewed counsel’s brief and the relevant portions of the record reflected therein. We concur with counsel’s assessment that the appeal presents no nonfrivolous issue *807for appellate review. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
